The sticker price gap narrows when you factor in total cost of ownership. BigCommerce's lower base rates get offset by:

- Required third-party apps for features Shopify includes natively
- Higher development costs for headless implementations
- POS subscription costs (not included)
- Integration middleware for inventory sync

At $1M+ annual GMV across 10 stores, expect to pay $35,000-$50,000/year on Shopify Plus versus $25,000-$40,000/year on BigCommerce Enterprise. The gap exists but isn't as dramatic as base pricing suggests.

